[FRONTEND APPLICATION INTERFACE]
│
│ (HTTP POST Payload with JSON + Cloudflare Turnstile Token)
▼
[CLOUDFLARE PAGES FUNCTIONS: /api/leads]
│
├───► [VALIDATION] Checks email syntax, string lengths, and inputs
├───► [TURNSTILE API] Securely calls Cloudflare verification endpoint to verify human status
│
▼
[CLOUDFLARE D1 SQL DATABASE] ──► Writes structured row: ID, email, origin, destination, timestamp
│
▲
│ (HTTP GET Request authenticated via Secure Bearer API Token authorization header)
[CLOUDFLARE PAGES FUNCTIONS: /api/reports/leads]
│
└───► [SQL SELECT QUERY] Streams structured database rows
└───► [CSV STREAM GENERATOR] Transforms dataset into a standards-compliant MIME spreadsheet
│
▼
[AUTOMATION / ADMIN DOWNLOAD]


## 2. Structural Source Code Blueprint

To eliminate runtime execution anomalies or agent context loss, the system code is organized into separate, modular logical blocks matching the Cloudflare Pages file structure convention exactly.

### File 1: Frontend Application UI (`/index.html`)
This file contains the complete semantic DOM structure, layout rendering engine (via Tailwind CSS CDN), interaction models, and automated asynchronous network transmission handlers. Save this file directly into the root directory of your project folder.

